    "The train ride home was different from the morning commute. In the morning, everyone was moving toward something—work, school, obligations. In the evening, everyone was moving away from something, and the energy in the train car was different. We were all escaping, if only for an hour, before we had to return to whatever lives we'd built for ourselves.",
    "The hospital was three stops from my apartment. I got off the train at 6:47 PM, exactly when I'd gotten off every day for two years. The walk to the hospital was familiar—turn left at the convenience store, pass the park where Yuna used to play, cross the street at the crosswalk where the traffic light always took too long to change. I could have walked it in my sleep. Sometimes I felt like I was.",
