    "The doctors called it a persistent vegetative state. They used words like 'brain activity' and 'neural responses' and 'probability of recovery' with the careful precision of people who'd learned that hope was a dangerous thing to give. I listened to every word. I researched every term. I became an expert in a field I never wanted to study.",
