    "Mom had a collection of cookbooks from around the world. Japanese, Italian, French, Mexican, Indian, Thai—she loved exploring different cuisines. I tried cooking some of her recipes, but they never tasted right. The ingredients were the same, the techniques were the same, but something was missing. The missing ingredient was her touch, her presence, her love. Without it, the food was just food. With it, it was magic.",
